/*Virtual Wall Activity Strings*/ Setup Name Create Routes /*Help Dialog Strings*/ Tips:
• Routes (or boulder problems) can be created by selecting holds on the wall as part of the route then clicking the add button at the bottom. \n
• Holds are selected by tapping on them on the virtual wall, which will cause a ring to be displayed around the selected hold. \n
• Routes will require two starting holds, which will be the first 2 holds the user selects. Start holds must be on row 5 or lower. When these holds are selected their rings are displayed as green. \n
• The user may then select any holds next as middle holds, as long as each hold they select is in a row higher than or in the same row as the previously selected hold. Also, they can only select 2 holds from the same row. They must select at least 2 middle holds. The middle holds will be highlighted with a blue ring. \n
• Once middle holds are selected, the user can select one finishing hold from any of the holds in the top row. The finishing hold is highlighted with a red ring. \n
• There is a Min of 5 holds and Max of 20 holds per route \n
